result.execSummary:
The defendant Tara N. Kauffman was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Drive or Operate Vehicle w/o Consent [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(3).
  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Tara N. Kauffman

records.addlTxt: Probation discharged- regular on 07/18/2020

(Cases 14CF901 and 17CF959 are called at 02:01 PM- all parties for this hearing appear via Zoom) Defendant Tara N. Kauffman in court, without counsel. Attorney Andrew Gunderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. DOC agent Elizabeth Pierce appeared. 
DOC agent Pierce indicates the Defendant has not completed some probation conditions: obtaining her GED and completing community service hours; however DOC asks that the remaining costs and fines be reduced to a civil judgment and probation not be revoked. Defendant makes a statement. State takes no position. 
Court orders probation will not be revoked and the remaining costs and fines are reduced to a civil judgment. (DOC to file necessary paperwork)
Review hearing on July 20, 2020 at 02:00 pm.

Dated 06/15/2020 from Department of Corrections Probation/Parole Agent Elizabeth Pierce to Court regarding request to either amend the Judgment of Conviction removing the uncompleted conditions or extend Ms. Kauffman's supervision.

Pursuant to the Supreme Courts Order issued 4/13/2020, this document is deemed filed 06/16/2020 because that is the date it was mailed.

(Cases called at 10:16 AM - 14CF901 and 17CF959)
Defendant Tara N. Kauffman in court without counsel.  Attorney Ellen Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Agent Elizabeth Pierce (DOC) appears by phone.  Court notes the concerns by the agent on the Defendant's lack of follow through on certain probation conditions.  Defendant provides argument in regards to appointments she has scheduled, plans for performing community service hours, and the goal of setting up a payment plan for restitution.  State makes argument for extending the Defendant's supervision to allow her to complete all of the requirements.  Agent Pierce makes additional comments.  Court orders a 6-month extension of probation, but if everything is done by January 2020, then Defendant can be discharged.

Dated 09/05/19 from Department of Corrections Probation/Parole Agent Elizabeth Pierce to Court regarding request for a Review Hearing prior to the defendant's discharge from Probation in January 2020.
Probation review hearing on September 27, 2019 at 10:15 am.
